<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>org.timepirate.commandoo</id>
  <name>commandoo</name>
  <summary>GUI and DB for gnu/linux command lines (CLI)</summary>
  
  <metadata_license>FSFAP</metadata_license>
  <project_license>LGPL-2.0-or-later</project_license>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      commandoo is a Graphical User Interface (GUI) for the Linux
    Command Line Interface (CLI), perhaps better known as the
    &quot;Terminal&quot;. 
    </p>
    <p>
      It&apos;s purpose is to give you a place to store the cool
    and/or useful command lines you find, discover, or create. Then,
    months later, when you need it again, it will be there, easy to
    find. 
    </p>
    <p>
      It creates, and supports, text based and sqlite databases,
    and comes with a basic database of over 160 linux commands. And
    many of the CL&apos;s can be run directly from the GUI. It also
    serves as a GUI app launcher.
    </p>
  </description>
  
  <launchable type="desktop-id">org.timepirate.commandoo.desktop</launchable>
